=You are a project management assistant. 
Extract task information from this support email and return ONLY valid JSON.

Email content: {{ $('Email Trigger (IMAP)').first().json.textPlain || $('Email Trigger (IMAP)').first().json.textHtml }}
Subject: {{ $('Email Trigger (IMAP)').first().json.metadata['thread-topic'] }}
Sender: {{ $('Email Trigger (IMAP)').first().json.metadata['return-path'] }}

Return this exact JSON structure:
{
  "title": "short task title (max 60 chars)",
  "description": "detailed description of the request",
  "prio": "urgent OR medium OR low",
  "dueDate": "YYYY-MM-DD (7 days from today if not specified)",
  "category": "Technical Task OR User Story",
  "subtasks": ["subtask item 1", "subtask item 2"],
  "createdBy": "sender email address"
}

For subtasks: if the email mentions specific steps, items or tasks to complete, list each as a string in the subtasks array. If none are mentioned, use an empty array [].

